task.summary: Default task
Minor adjustments and testing
added make_possible_edge_list() to Roller
tdRoller now accounts for edges that don't have meaningful importance scores
Basic plotting added to make a figure for Neda
Basic plotting added to make a figure for Neda. Mostly useless
Added edge ranking
Edges are now ranked based on adjusted importance score (adj_imp), which is weighted by p_value

Fix method for getting coefficients
The get_coeffs method did not function correctly for minimum lags greater than zero. Changes to the function _fitstack_coeffs were necessary as well

Add MSE calculations during model building in tdRFRWindow
If the MSE of the full model is lower than the MSE of the model without the particular explanatory variable, then that edge should be in the model. If it is not higher than it should be eliminated.
Fix window labelling issue when making the edge table
Fix mse calculations when allowing min lag of 0

Fix function options to calculate mse when desired
The argument calc_mse gets passed through many objects and functions, but the code should run faster when that is set to False. The MSE calculations will be skipped
Change kwarg to all be calc_mse

Change name from Roller to Swing
First commit on the new branch. Change names of classes and files from Roller to Swing. Keep original folder directory as Roller to prevent issues with Git. This can be changed later
Change usage of tdRoller, Roller, and tdSwing to Swing
Replace additional occurrences of Swing_old with Swing

Change default arguments for Swing object
All parameters that a user might want to change should be set when the object is initialized. These can be changed later when creating windows. Future work should make methods for handling this
Change make_possible_edge list to static method

Modify create_windows method explicit FOR loop and delete get_window method
The number of windows generated will likely be small and the list comprehension will not affect the speed a lot. The explicit FOR will make for easier changes in the future if different data needs to be passed for time delays
Remove redundant get_window_object methods
Add method to check if lags meet criteria
Add additional criteria for lags to meet. Add methods to set min and max lag
Calculate the explanatory indices of time delayed windows before creating each window
Change SWING so that it assigns appropriate explanatory and response data to each window during creation
Change arguments for Windows to accept uniform variables

Remove method augment_windows
This is unnecessary because all data is now passed to each window during creation

Remove references to include_window
This is an unnecessary attribute
Refactor fit and rank methods for RFRWindow

Remove class tdRFRWindow
No longer necessary
Remove old score method
Remove unecessary methods from RFRWindow

Remove function plot_scoring
Resolves issue #13

Move abstract methods to bottom of Window methods
Resolves issue #8

Refactor possible_edge_list methods
These were streamlined to one method and placed in the utility module. Partially resolves issue #7
Test cragging. Appears to work for RFRWindow

Remove update_variance method in LassoWindow
It appeared redundant with the parent method. No need to overrie
Update display progress code while fitting windows
Refactor Lasso get_coeffs and methods that call it

Remove old make_edge_table method
Not used any longer

Remove tdLassoWindow class. Refactor make_edge_table.
The child class should no longer be necessary. The refactor of the make_edge_table helps the results mimic those in randomforest
Move method _initialize_coeffs to class Window

Move method sum_of_squares to utility module
This is shared by many methods but is a static method

Remove update_variance_2D from DionesusWindow
Exists in the parent window

Update Dionesus methods. NOT Complete
This commit partially through refactoring, so that some of the code can be used
Refactor Dionesus methods. Remove tdDionesus methods

Pandas v0.17 does not allow boolean comparisons with tuples
Of particular interest is line 617 in Swing.py. This needs to be checked in future versions
Generate in silico data from Gene Net Weaver
Add in silico subnetworks extracted from GNW

Generate unique graphs from GNW
Code still needs to be cleaned, but this seems to work.
